# Nuxt Boilerplate – Coding Rules

## Architecture: Feature-Based

```
app/features/<name>/
├── components/    # Components used only within this feature
├── composables/   # useFeature.ts – logic bridge between store and components
├── stores/        # useFeatureStore.ts – Pinia setup store
├── models/        # Pinia ORM entity models
├── types/         # feature.types.ts – interfaces and types
└── locales/       # en.json – i18n strings
```

- Pages are thin: only call feature components, set `definePageMeta`
- Cross-feature UI → `app/components/shared/` (auto-prefixed as `App*`)
- Global state → `app/stores/` only (theme, auth session)
- Global composables → `app/composables/` only (e.g. `useApi`)

## TypeScript

- Use TypeScript only, fully strict types
- `strict: true` — never disable
- **No `any`** — define an explicit type or interface instead
- All function parameters and return values must be typed
- Feature types → `features/<name>/types/<name>.types.ts`
- Global types → `app/types/index.ts`, domain types → `app/types/<domain>.types.ts`
- **Never define inline types in stores, composables, or components** — import from types file

## No Code Comments

Self-documenting names only. No inline comments, no JSDoc blocks.
Exception: `// TODO:` for intentional stubs only.

## i18n

- All UI strings via `$t()` / `useI18n()` — never hardcode text
- Locale files: `features/<name>/locales/en.json`
- Global strings: `app/shared/locales/en.json`
- Auto-namespaced: `auth` feature → `$t('auth.login.title')`
- English only (`en`)

## Pinia

- Setup store style always: `defineStore('name', () => { ... })`
- State typed with `ref<Type>`, not `ref(null)` without generic
- Feature stores → `features/<name>/stores/useFeatureStore.ts`
- Global stores → `app/stores/useAppStore.ts`

## Pinia ORM

- Entity models → `features/<name>/models/ModelName.ts`
- Use typed decorators: `@Num(0)`, `@Str('')`, `@Bool(false)`
- Access via `useRepo(ModelName)` in stores or composables

## SCSS & Theme System

- Themes → `app/assets/scss/themes/`, one file per theme (`_default.scss`, `_dark.scss`, `_ocean.scss`)
- Each theme uses `[data-theme='<name>']` with HSL primary color tokens (`--color-primary-h/s/l`)
- `_variables.scss` contains **only** non-color tokens (spacing, typography, radii)
- User custom color → override `--color-primary-h/s/l` at runtime via `useThemeStore.setCustomColor(hex)`
- Adding a theme: create SCSS file → add `ThemeId` union → add to `THEME_OPTIONS` → import in `main.scss`
- Components: `<style scoped lang="scss">` in this exact order, BEM naming, CSS vars only — no hardcoded values

## Nuxt Auto-Imports (do not import manually)

- Vue: `ref`, `computed`, `reactive`, `watch`, `onMounted`, …
- Nuxt: `definePageMeta`, `useHead`, `navigateTo`, `useRoute`, `useRouter`, `createError`, `defineNuxtRouteMiddleware`, …
- Pinia: `defineStore`
- All composables from `app/composables/` and `app/features/*/composables/`
- All stores from `app/stores/` and `app/features/*/stores/`

## Server

- `server/api/<name>.<method>.ts` — use `defineEventHandler`
- Return typed objects only

## Git Commits – Conventional Commits

Format: `type(scope): short description`

| Type | When to use |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New feature or page |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change with no behavior change |
| `style` | Formatting only (no logic change) |
| `docs` | Documentation, README, agent rules |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `chore` | Tooling, config, dependencies |
| `build` | Build system changes (nuxt.config, vite) |
| `ci` | CI/CD pipeline changes |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `revert` | Revert a previous commit |

**Scope** = affected feature or area (`auth`, `home`, `i18n`, `deps`, `layout`)

```
feat(auth): add login page and auth store
fix(home): correct hero subtitle alignment
chore(deps): update nuxt to 4.4.5
refactor(auth): extract login logic into useAuth composable
test(home): add HomeHero component integration test
build(nuxt): enable pinia-orm module
```

- Subject: max 72 chars, lowercase, no trailing period
- Body (optional): explain *why*, not *what*
- Breaking change: `feat(auth)!: remove legacy session`
